# Contributing

Keep repository-docs changes small, boundary-first, and placed by role.

## Where To Change

- Route instructions: `AGENTS.md`
- Index and placement guidance: `README`-class files
- Current canonical structure and placement guidance: `Docs/Architecture/*`
- Design-in-progress: `Docs/Proposals/*` when that subtree is present
- Historical record: `Docs/Decisions/*`, `Docs/Migrations/*`, and
  `Docs/Archive/*` when those subtrees are present
- Reference material and supporting examples: `Docs/Reference/*` when that
  subtree is present
- GitHub-facing governance and collaboration files: `.github/*`
- Repo-wide contributor policy: root governance files such as `CONTRIBUTING.md`

## Placement Discipline

- Keep route instructions in `AGENTS.md`.
- Keep repository and subtree indexes in `README`-class files.
- Keep current canonical structure in `Docs/Architecture/*`.
- Keep design-in-progress in `Docs/Proposals/*` when that subtree is present.
- Keep historical material in `Docs/Decisions/*`, `Docs/Migrations/*`, and
  `Docs/Archive/*` when those subtrees are present.
- Keep GitHub-facing collaboration files in `.github/`.
